{"tid":928711,"cid":6,"subCid":0,"title":"普捷天奴：阿仙奴捧左盃先準係更衣室自拍慶祝！","createTime":"2018-12-05T05:03:23.000Z","updateTime":"2018-12-05T11:53:23.000Z","uid":19527,"like":7,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":28,"replies":[{"pid":"59ccd56fa70c33756890d00c49a360a1444506d2","tid":928711,"uid":19527,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-12-05T05:03:23.000Z","msg":"MAURICIO POCHETTINO has told his Spurs stars: No dressing-room selfies until we win a trophy.<br />\n<br />\nJubilant Arsenal players posted a photo after crushing Tottenham 4-2 in Sunday&rsquo;s North London derby.<br />\n<br />\nBut Poch snapped: &ldquo;Obviously if you win a trophy like I did when I was a player, it is time to celebrate.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;Of course, show the fans you are happy, it&rsquo;s fantastic &mdash; but when you win something special.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;I accept people need it. It is how you feed your ego and I accept it is a new world. But I am of the older generation and, personally, I don&rsquo;t like them.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;This is my mentality. I accept new technology but I try to keep a bit of that away.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;I love to celebrate the things with your team-mates but I love to celebrate in private and not make it public.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nPoch, 46, who won two Spanish Cup finals as a defender with Espanyol, admits he is baffled at people feeling the need to get out their phones to take snaps &mdash; at times like when he is walking his pet pooch Sansa in a local park."},{"pid":"0b930649c821d9fe879bbab7bc65e4785e0c1143","tid":928711,"uid":19527,"like":44,"dislike":1,"score":43,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2018-12-05T05:03:51.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"https://www.thesportreview.com/wp-content/uploads/alli-son500.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thesportreview.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Falli-son500.jpg&h=81b7613f&s={SIZE}\" />"},{"pid":"ab8ce56eeaefcfdc89fe8fa18c977ab7bcbba1cb","tid":928711,"uid":96182,"lik